guage\"}, {\"begin\": 349, \"end\": 361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.7347732204720636, \"rank\": 0.3609641343770274, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"astatementreleased Saturday\", \"from\": 239, \"to\": 266}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"scenes\", \"from\": 310, \"to\": 321}, {\"ngram\": \"derision\", \"from\": 325, \"to\": 333}, {\"ngram\": \"mockery\", \"from\": 338, \"to\": 345}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We thank the members of other religious denominations who have expressed their solidarity.\", \"from\": 390, \"to\": 481, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the members\", \"from\": 400, \"to\": 411}, {\"ngram\": \"other religious denominations\", \"from\": 415, \"to\": 444}, {\"ngram\": \"their solidarity\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 480}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This morning, we think of all Christians on all continents who have been hurt by the outrage and provocation of certain scenes,\\\" the French bishops said.\", \"from\": 482, \"to\": 635, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 512, \"end\": 522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.7637188044518357, \"rank\": 0.30453245705557663, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 615, \"end\": 621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7871183017600282, \"rank\": 0.2703955556991689, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all continents\", \"from\": 526, \"to\": 540}, {\"ngram\": \"the outrage\", \"from\": 563, \"to\": 574}, {\"ngram\": \"provocation\", \"from\": 579, \"to\": 590}, {\"ngram\": \"certain scenes\", \"from\": 594, \"to\": 608}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the best-known prelates of the Catholic Church in the United States, Bishop Robert Barron of Winona-Rochester, Minnesota, called on Catholics to \\\"make their voices heard\\\" in response to what he called \\\"the gross mockery of the Last Supper.\\\"\", \"from\": 637, \"to\": 884, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 675, \"end\": 690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999998894964, \"rank\": 1.1045266244577406e-10, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 698, \"end\": 711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999939337705933, \"rank\": 6.066240916217788e-06, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 720, \"end\": 733, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Barron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.396820994598482e-29, \"text\": \"Robert Barron\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Barron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_Barron\"}, {\"begin\": 737, \"end\": 753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Catholic_Diocese_of_Winona\\u2013Rochester\", \"score\": 0.9892654137746267, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Winona-Rochester\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Catholic_Diocese_of_Winona\\u2013Rochester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roman_Catholic_Diocese_of_Winona\\u2013Rochester\"}, {\"begin\": 755, \"end\": 764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota\", \"score\": 0.999999954256965, \"rank\": 2.7519274104918015e-08, \"text\": \"Minnesota\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Minnesota\"}, {\"begin\": 776, \"end\": 785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.0750444467650973e-12, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the best-known prelates\", \"from\": 644, \"to\": 667}, {\"ngram\": \"their voices\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 807}, {\"ngram\": \"response\", \"from\": 818, \"to\": 826}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"the gross mockery\", \"from\": 845, \"to\": 863}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 867, \"to\": 882}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a post on X, Barron said the blasphemous act was emblematic of a \\\"deeply secularist postmodern society\\\" that identifies Christianity as its enemy.\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 1035, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 902, \"end\": 908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\", \"score\": 0.999999999964075, \"rank\": 3.6031950891467376e-11, \"text\": \"Barron\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Family_of_Donald_Trump\"}, {\"begin\": 1009, \"end\": 1021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.7347732204720636, \"rank\": 0.3609641343770274, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a post\", \"from\": 889, \"to\": 895}, {\"ngram\": \"X\", \"from\": 899, \"to\": 900}, {\"ngram\": \"the blasphemous act\", \"from\": 914, \"to\": 933}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"deeply secularist postmodern society\", \"from\": 952, \"to\": 991}, {\"ngram\": \"its enemy\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1034}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile,in reparation for the blasphemy, Bishop Donald Hying of Madison, Wisconsin, immediately called on all Catholics to \\\"fast and pray, renew our devotion to the Eucharist, the Sacred Heart, and the Virgin Mary.\\\"\", \"from\": 1037, \"to\": 1254, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1080, \"end\": 1086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"score\": 0.9750631687329239, \"rank\": 0.025574580259751904, \"text\": \"Bishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\"}, {\"begin\": 1112, \"end\": 1121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wisconsin\", \"score\": 0.9999980093968392, \"rank\": 1.9779822761219868e-06, \"text\": \"Wisconsin\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wisconsin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wisconsin\"}, {\"begin\": 1149, \"end\": 1158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.0750444467650973e-12, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 1204, \"end\": 1213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"score\": 0.9999991459266321, \"rank\": 8.533545891105419e-07, \"text\": \"Eucharist\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\"}, {\"begin\": 1241, \"end\": 1252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veneration_of_Mary_in_the_Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999219030572, \"rank\": 7.809716652612092e-08, \"text\": \"Virgin Mary\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veneration_of_Mary_in_the_Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Veneration_of_Mary_in_the_Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"reparation\", \"from\": 1050, \"to\": 1060}, {\"ngram\": \"the blasphemy\", \"from\": 1065, \"to\": 1078}, {\"ngram\": \"Madison\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1110}, {\"ngram\": \"our devotion\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1196}, {\"ngram\": \"the Sacred Heart\", \"from\": 1215, \"to\": 1231}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"May Jesus be adored and loved in every tabernacle throughout the world,\\\" Hying added in a post on X in which he thanked the Lord for the Eucharist, the Last Supper, and his \\\"love for us.\\\"\", \"from\": 1256, \"to\": 1444, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1261, \"end\": 1266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.999998788776617, \"rank\": 1.211224957418255e-06, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 1394, \"end\": 1403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"score\": 0.9999991459266321, \"rank\": 8.533545891105419e-07, \"text\": \"Eucharist\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eucharist\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"every tabernacle\", \"from\": 1290, \"to\": 1306}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1318, \"to\": 1327}, {\"ngram\": \"Hying\", \"from\": 1330, \"to\": 1335}, {\"ngram\": \"a post\", \"from\": 1345, \"to\": 1351}, {\"ngram\": \"X\", \"from\": 1355, \"to\": 1356}, {\"ngram\": \"the Lord\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1385}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 1405, \"to\": 1420}, {\"ngram\": \"his \\\"love\", \"from\": 1426, \"to\": 1435}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1440, \"to\": 1442}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bishop Daniel Flores of Brownsville, Texas, was also quick to share his reaction, stating: \\\"My vocabulary is not varied enough to find a word for the feeling in the pit of my stomach.\\\"\", \"from\": 1446, \"to\": 1630, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1446, \"end\": 1452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"score\": 0.9750631687329239, \"rank\": 0.025574580259751904, \"text\": \"Bishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\"}, {\"begin\": 1453, \"end\": 1466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danny_Flores\", \"score\": 0.9987788790239297, \"rank\": 0.0012226134258934444, \"text\": \"Daniel Flores\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danny_Flores\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Danny_Flores\"}, {\"begin\": 1470, \"end\": 1488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_of_Brownsville\", \"score\": 0.9999839886790489, \"rank\": 1.6011577120479105e-05, \"text\": \"Brownsville, Texas\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_of_Brownsville\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_of_Brownsville\"}, {\"begin\": 1470, \"end\": 1488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_of_Brownsville\", \"score\": 0.9999839886790489, \"rank\": 1.6011577120479105e-05, \"text\": \"Brownsville, Texas\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_of_Brownsville\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Port_of_Brownsville\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"his reaction\", \"from\": 1514, \"to\": 1526}, {\"ngram\": \"My vocabulary\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1551}, {\"ngram\": \"a word\", \"from\": 1581, \"to\": 1587}, {\"ngram\": \"the feeling\", \"from\": 1592, \"to\": 1603}, {\"ngram\": \"the pit\", \"from\": 1607, \"to\": 1614}, {\"ngram\": \"my stomach\", \"from\": 1618, \"to\": 1628}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He also asserted that people of Christian faith \\\"deserve more respect.\\\"\", \"from\": 1631, \"to\": 1702, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1663, \"end\": 1672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.998901429249465, \"rank\": 0.001099778935478597, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1659}, {\"ngram\": \"more respect\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1700}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Flores' sentiments were also echoed by non-Christians.\", \"from\": 1704, \"to\": 1758, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Flores' sentiments\", \"from\": 1704, \"to\": 1722}, {\"ngram\": \"non\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1746}, {\"ngram\": \"Christians\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1757}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Even as a Jew, I am infuriated by this outrageous insult to Jesus and Christianity,\\\"Eli Davidsaid.\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1859, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1771, \"end\": 1774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"score\": 0.9986789956101548, \"rank\": 0.0013227517269187245, \"text\": \"Jew\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\"}, {\"begin\": 1821, \"end\": 1826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 0.999998788776617, \"rank\": 1.211224957418255e-06, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 1831, \"end\": 1843, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.7347732204720636, \"rank\": 0.3609641343770274, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this outrageous insult\", \"from\": 1795, \"to\": 1817}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He panned the opening ceremonies as reflecting a Europe that is \\\"culturally dying.\\\"\", \"from\": 1860, \"to\": 1943, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{